```xml
<output>
<analysis>
<has-cmf>The post does not contain a CMF number.  While the absence of a CMF number doesn't automatically exclude it from being electoral propaganda, it suggests it might not be directly linked to an official campaign.</has-cmf>
<refers-to-candidate>The post does not refer to any specific parliamentary candidate by name or affiliation. It mentions "România de astăzi" (Romania of today), which is a general reference and not specific to any candidate or party.</refers-to-candidate>
<addresses-the-wide-population>The post is a paid Facebook advertisement, inherently designed to reach a wide audience.  The targeting parameters (age, location) further confirm this intention.</addresses-the-wide-population>
<electoral-objective>The content of the post is a reflection on the significance of December 1st, Romania's National Day. While patriotic in nature, it lacks any explicit or implicit endorsement of a particular candidate or party for the parliamentary elections. There is no call to action related to voting.</electoral-objective>
<journalism>The post could be considered a form of citizen journalism, expressing a personal reflection on a national holiday. It doesn't present itself as objective news reporting but rather as a personal opinion piece.</journalism>
<personal_opinion>The post expresses a personal opinion about the meaning of December 1st for Romania. This is not intended to influence the vote in the parliamentary elections.</personal_opinion>
</analysis>

<conclusion>
<post_id>944738014199665</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
The Facebook post, while politically themed, does not constitute electoral propaganda under Article 98 t) of LEGE nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015.  The post focuses on a reflection about Romania's National Day, December 1st, and does not promote or discourage voting for any specific candidate or party participating in the parliamentary elections.  The lack of a CMF number further weakens any argument for it being electoral propaganda.  The post's objective appears to be to express a personal sentiment about a national holiday, not to influence the outcome of the elections.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>FALSE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
<electoral-propaganda-candidates/>
<responsible-party-or-group>Narcis Constantin</responsible-party-or-group>
<message-for-police/>
</conclusion>
</output>
```
